From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Fri, 19 Jun 2026 18:34:32 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] findutils: reduce vendored crate to a find-only library
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Drop the locate/updatedb/xargs/testing modules and binaries, their
benches, and the dev-dependencies — sarun vendors findutils only to run
`find` in-process. lib.rs now exposes just `pub mod find`; Cargo.toml is
a lean library manifest (find's runtime deps: argmax, chrono, clap,
faccess, nix, onig, regex, uucore 0.9, walkdir, itertools, thiserror).

Builds clean as a library (cargo build --lib). No behavioral change to
find itself; this is purely scope reduction ahead of the in-process
adaptation.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01B5MwFcipu6iwqtMPPwFhXd
